claim.claim-text:
1. A method comprising: 
providing an integrated circuit having a top layer of metal; 
forming an on-chip decoupling capacitor stack on the top layer of metal; 
forming a bump contact contacting the capacitor stack; and 
reducing a voltage droop on a power grid.

17. An apparatus comprising: 
an integrated circuit having a top metal layer; 
the top metal layer having a plurality of lines with a plurality of purposes; 
a decoupling capacitor coupled to a first top metal line; 
a bump coupled to the decoupling capacitor and a second top metal line having a different purpose than the first top metal line coupled to the capacitor wherein the bump provides power to the second metal line and electrically decouples the first metal line.
